com.google.flightmap.android.map
Class MapPresenter

java.lang.Object
  com.google.flightmap.android.map.MapPresenter
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.content.SharedPreferences.OnSharedPreferenceChangeListener
public class MapPresenter
extends Object
implements android.content.SharedPreferences.OnSharedPreferenceChangeListener

Presenter part of Model-View-Presenter for the map display.

All the non-trivial UI work is done here.

See Also:
MapModel, MapView

getLocationForPoint

private LatLng getLocationForPoint(float zoom,
                                   float orientation,
                                   android.graphics.Point anchorPoint,
                                   android.graphics.Point screenPoint)
Returns ground position corresponding to screenPoint.

Parameters:
zoom - zoom level.
orientation - bearing in degrees from locationPoint to the top center of the screen. Will be 0 when north-up, and the current track when track-up.
anchorPoint - pixel coordinates of anchor location (in Mercator pixel space as returned by AndroidMercatorProjection.toPoint(double, com.google.flightmap.common.data.LatLng)
screenPoint - coordinates in screen pixel space (such as from a touch event).

getLocationForPoint

private LatLng getLocationForPoint(android.graphics.Point screenPoint)
Returns ground position corresponding to screenPoint. Uses mapAnchorLatLng for location and lastBearing for orientation and calls getLocationForPoint(float, float, Point, Point).

Parameters:
screenPoint - coordinates in screen pixel space (such as from a touch event).
Returns:
ground position, or null if mapAnchorLatLng is null.

                                                   android.graphics.Point anchorPoint,
                                                   LatLng location)
Returns screen pixel coordinates corresponding to location.

Parameters:

anchorPoint - pixel coordinates of anchor location (in Mercator pixel space as returned by AndroidMercatorProjection.toPoint(double, com.google.flightmap.common.data.LatLng)
location - location to convert to a screen point.

getPointForLocation

private android.graphics.Point getPointForLocation(LatLng location)
Returns screen pixel coordinates corresponding to location. Uses lastBearing for orientation.

Parameters:
location - ground location to map to screen pixel coordinates.
Returns:
screen pixel coordinates, or null if mapAnchorLatLng is null.

chooseSingleAirport

private Airport chooseSingleAirport(Collection<Airport> airports)
Returns single airport from airports. If the collection has exactly one item, that Airport will be returned. Otherwise a dialog box will be shown so the user can choose an airport.

Parameters:
airports - airports to choose from. May not be null or empty.
